<item>
            <title>[LU-16519] rename/link/merge mdt.*.md_stats to mdt.*.stats</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16519</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is an &lt;tt&gt;mdt.&amp;#42;.md_stats&lt;/tt&gt; file for each MDT, but every other device type has just a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;type&amp;gt;.&amp;#42;.stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; file to report statistics.  The &lt;tt&gt;md_stats&lt;/tt&gt; file format is the same as other &lt;tt&gt;stats&lt;/tt&gt; files so there is no good reason to use the same name.  There was historically an &quot;obd stats&quot; file for the MDT, but that no longer exists.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the client, there are &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mdc.&amp;#42;.md_stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lmv.&amp;#42;.md_stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; files alongside the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#42;.&amp;#42;.stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; files, which partly contain duplicate statistics, and partly different statistics.  There doesn&apos;t seem to be a particularly good reason for the separation.  There is also &quot;&lt;tt&gt;mdc.&amp;#42;.mdc_stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; which contains &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lockless_read_bytes&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lockless_write_bytes&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, which I don&apos;t think is very useful today.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
